ates over the different meanings of co-operation can also illuminate broader questions about the emergence of consumer interests in the first half of the twentieth century, especially in a transnational context.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aConsumer cooperativeszEurope, NorthernxHistoryy19th century. 0aConsumer cooperativeszEurope, NorthernxHistoryy20th century. 0aCooperationzEurope, NorthernxHistoryy19th century. 0aCooperationzEurope, NorthernxHistoryy20th century. 0aCooperative societieszEurope, NorthernxHistoryy19th century. 0aCooperative societieszEurope, NorthernxHistoryy20th century. 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic History.2bisacsh  aCo-operation.  aCo-operative movement.  aInter-war period.  aInternational Co-operative Alliance (ICA).  aInternationalism.  aNordic countries.1 aHilson, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612733440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526127334423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526127334/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles